Haashim Domingo of Mamelodi Sundowns during the DStv Premiership 2021/22 match between TS Galaxy and Mamelodi Sundowns held at Mbombela Stadium in Nelspruit on 02 March 2022 SOWETO - Orlando Pirates settled for a share of the spoils against Cape Town City on Wednesday at the Orlando Stadium. Elsewhere, Mamelodi Sundowns continue to push for their successive fifth league title, following their win over TS Galaxy at the Mbombela Stadium last night. The Brazilians returned from Caf Champions League duties, where they recorded their first-ever win on Egyptian soil against Al Ahly. Last night, they beat the Rockets 3-0 to open an 18-point gap at the top of the table, with just eight games until the end of the season.